l=https://venturebeat.com/2014/07/22/chinese-smartphone-maker-xiaomi-launches-sleek-new-phone-and-13-fitness-band/|title=Chinese smartphone maker Xiaomi launches sleek new phone and $13 fitness band|work=VentureBeat|accessdate=16 May 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160430063108/http://venturebeat.com/2014/07/22/chinese-smartphone-maker-xiaomi-launches-sleek-new-phone-and-13-fitness-band/|archivedate=30 April 2016|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> With 2.8 million Mi Band shipments in the first quarter of 2015, Xiaomi became the world's second-largest wearables maker, accounting for 24.6% of the global market share.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2015/jun/04/xiaomi-worlds-second-biggest-wearables-maker|title=Xiaomi now world's second-biggest wearables maker|last1=Gibbs|first1=Samuel|date=4 June 2015|work=The Guardian|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161209182010/https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2015/jun/04/xiaomi-worlds-second-biggest-wearables-maker|archivedate=9 December 2016|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nXiaomi announced the Mi Band 2 in June 2016.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theverge.com/circuitbreaker/2016/6/2/11840394/xiaomi-mi-band-2-official|title=Xiaomi officially launches the Mi Band 2|work=The Verge|access-date=24 November 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201040358/https://www.theverge.com/circuitbreaker/2016/6/2/11840394/xiaomi-mi-band-2-official|archivedate=1 December 2017|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Mi Band 2 features [[Photoplethysmogram|PPG]] sensor for accurate heart rate tracking. It also uses an upgraded pedometer algorithm for gathering better fitness and sleep data. The Mi Band 2's housing was rated for [[IP67]] water resistance.\n\nThe Mi Band 3 was released 18 July 2018. It has a larger battery, larger screen and improved water resistance.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.techadvisor.co.uk/new-product/wearable-tech/xiaomi-mi-band-3-3678215/|title=Pre-order the Mi Band 3 fitness tracker|last=Macro|first=Ashleigh|work=Tech Advisor|access-date=2018-08-03|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref name=\"Xiaomi Mi Band 3 review\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.techradar.com/uk/reviews/xiaomi-mi-band-3-review|title=Xiaomi Mi Band 3 review|work=TechRadar|access-date=2018-08-03|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://geek360.com.br/melhores-smartbands/|title=Melhores Smartbands do Mercado, Atualizado para 2019 - Geek360|date=2018-10-10|website=Geek 360|language=pt-BR|access-date=2019-03-04}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Model\n!Design\n!Display\n!Specifications\n!Release Date\n|-\n|[[Xiaomi Mi Band|Mi Band]]<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.mi.com/en/miband/|title=Mi Band - Mi Global Home|publisher=mi.com|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170825144318/http://www.mi.com/en/miband/|archivedate=25 August 2017|url-status=live|access-date=5 September 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|[[File:Mi_Band.jpg|150x150px|Mi Band]]\n|3 LED Multi Color\n|[[Pedometer]], Vibration\n|22 July 2014\n|-\n|[[Xiaomi Mi Band#Xiaomi Mi Band Pulse|Mi Band 1S]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mi.com/shouhuan/spec/|title=\u5c0f\u7c73\u667a\u80fd\u624b\u73af\u53c2\u6570 - \u5c0f\u7c73\u5546\u57ce|publisher=mi.com|language=zh-CN|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170904063944/http://www.mi.com/shouhuan/spec/|archivedate=4 September 2017|url-status=live|access-date=5 September 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|[[File:Xiaomi_Mi_Band_Black.jpg|150x150px|Xiaomi Mi Band 1s]]\n|3 LED White\n|Pedometer, Heart Rate Monitor, Vibration\n|7 November 2015\n|-\n|[[Xiaomi Mi Band 2|Mi Band 2]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mi.com/en/miband2/|title=Mi Band 2 - Mi Global Home|date=10 November 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161110085242/http://www.mi.com/en/miband2/|archivedate=10 November 2016|url-status=bot: unknown|access-date=29 January 2017}}</ref>\n|[[File:Xiaomi Mi band 2 18.jpg|frameless]]\n|0,42\" [[OLED]], [[Monochromatic]]\n|Watch, Heart Rate Monitor, Pedometer, Vibration, [[Touchpad]]\n|7 June 2016\n|-\n|Mi Band - HRX Edition<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mi.com/in/mi-band-hrx/|title=Mi India|publisher=mi.com|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171027231945/http://www.mi.com/in/mi-band-hrx/|archivedate=27 October 2017|url-status=live|access-date=27 October 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|\n|0,42\" OLED, Monochromatic\n|Watch, Pedometer, Vibration, Touchpad\n|15 September 2017 (India)\n|-\n|[[Xiaomi Mi Band 3|Mi Band 3]]\n|[[File:Mi Band 3 NFC.jpeg|frameless]]\n|0.78\" [[OLED]], [[Monochromatic]]\n|Watch, Heart Rate Monitor, Pedometer, Vibration, [[Touchpad]], NFC (limited models)<ref name=\"Xiaomi Mi Band 3 review\"/>\n|18 July 2018\n|-\n|[[Xiaomi Mi Band 4|Mi Band 4]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gizmochina.com/2019/06/11/xiaomi-mi-band-4-officially-launched/|title=Xiaomi Mi Band 4 officially launched with AMOLED color Display & Cheap Price tag|last=Jaszly|first=Airyl|date=2019-06-11|website=Gizmochina|language=en-US|access-date=2019-06-12}}</ref>\n|\n|0.95\" [[AMOLED]]<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.mi.com/shouhuan4/specs/|title=\u5c0f\u7c73\u624b\u73af4 \u53c2\u6570-\u5c0f\u7c73\u5546\u57ce|website=www.mi.com|access-date=2019-06-12}}</ref>\n|Watch, Heart Rate Monitor, Pedometer, Vibration, [[Touchpad]], [[Near-field communication|NFC]] (some models)<ref name=\":1\" />\n|14 June 2019 (China)\n26 June 2019 (Europe)\n|}\n\n== Mechanical Watch ==\nXiaomi released a mechanical watch called the CIGA Automatic Mechanical Watch. It has a square shape with rounded corners. The body is stainless steel and comes with a choice of black or silver. The watch comes with a metal mesh band or a leather strap. The mechanical movement is made by Seagull watch company. The watch was designed by Hong-Kong-based Michael Young and has won the German IF Design award.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.xiaomitoday.com/xiaomi-ciga-automatic-mechanical-watch-offered-for-180-99coupon/|title=Xiaomi CIGA Automatic Mechanical Watch Offered For $159.74|date=2018-09-19|work=XiaomiToday|access-date=2018-09-21|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== Smart Home Products ==\n{{Main|Xiaomi Smart Home}}\n<!-- Insert summary of main article -->\nNote that products released by ''Xiaomi Smart Home'' are products of companies partnered with Xiaomi instead of Xiaomi themselves.<ref>[https://www.androidcentral.com/these-are-best-xiaomi-lifestyle-products-you-can-buy These are the best Xiaomi lifestyle products you can buy in 2018]</ref>\nIncludes [[robotic vacuum cleaner]]s and other goods.\n\nMi Home app  manages Xiaomi [[smart home]] products.\n\n== Mi Drone ==\nThe Mi Drone has a [[1080p]] camera and a [[4K resolution|4K camera]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mi.com/en/drone/|title=Mi Global Home|website=www.mi.com|language=en-EN|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180127084204/http://www.mi.com/en/drone/|archivedate=27 January 2018|url-status=live|access-date=26 January 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref> It has a range of 2km while able to maintain a [[720p]] video stream.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.engadget.com/2016/05/25/xiaomi-mi-drone/|title=Xiaomi's Mi Drone is pretty affordable for what it does|work=Engadget|access-date=2018-09-26|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n\n\n==See also==\n*[[History of Xiaomi]]\n*[https://kyadomain.blogspot.com/2019/06/redmi-note-8-pro-specifications.html?m=1 Xiaomi '''note 8 pro''' specifications]\n*[https://kyadomain.blogspot.com/2019/05/Xiaomi-Black-Shark-2-Gaming-Smartphone-Launch-Pricing-and-Specifications.html Gaming smartphones of Xiaomi]\n*\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Xiaomi]]\n[[Category:Lists of mobile phones|Xiaomi]]\n[[Category:Lists of products|Xiaomi]]\n[[Category:Lists of mobile computers|Xiaomi]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox company\n| logo = Xiaomi logo.svg\n| logo_size = 120px\n| founder = [[Lei Jun]]\n| products = Mi Tv <br />\n\nMi NoteBook <br />\n\nMi Band <br />\n\nMi drone <br />\n\nMi WiFi <br />\n\nMi Box <br />\n\nRedmi <br />\n\nPoco <br />\n| foundation = {{start date and age|2010|04|06|df=y}}\n}}\n[[Xiaomi]] produces smartphones (Mi Series, Mi Note Series, Mi Max Series, Mi Mix Series and [[Redmi|Redmi Series]]), tablets, laptops, wearable devices, TVs, routers and other smart home devices on their web store and on third-party websites.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-04-09/xiaomi-confronts-counterfeits-as-fake-products-eat-into-sales|title=Xiaomi Confronts Counterfeits as Fake Products Eat Into Sales - Bloomberg Business|date=10 April 2015|publisher=Bloomberg L.P.|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150413082926/http://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-04-09/xiaomi-confronts-counterfeits-as-fake-products-eat-into-sales |archivedate=13 April 2015|url-status=live|accessdate=28 February 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Some of their products are listed below.\n\n<!--Please do not include devices made by Xiaomi-affiliated manufacturers in the list (e.g., Xiaomi Smart Home, Xiaomi Life, Mijia, Xiaomi Ecosystem, Xiaomi Shengtailian, Xiaomi Youpin, Xiaomi Crowdfunding), they are not manufactured by Xiaomi itself.-->\n\n== Smartphones ==\n=== MIUI ===\n{{Main|MIUI}}Xiaomi's smartphones run MIUI. [[MIUI]] is a stock and aftermarket Android firmware for [[smartphones]] and [[tablet computers]] based on the [[open-source]] [[Android (operating system)|Android]] [[operating system]]. It is available on Xiaomi devices as well as devices made by other companies. It is Xiaomi's earliest known product.\n\n=== Mi Series ===\nXiaomi's flagship mobile handset line is the Xiaomi Mi series.\n\nThe Mi 3 uses a modified [[Qualcomm Snapdragon]] 800 and was found on test to be the world's fastest Android smartphone according to [[Benchmark (computing)|benchmark]] testing apps [[Antutu]], Quadrant, and [[Geekbench]].<ref>{{citation|title=Xiaomi - Google+ - A comparison between # XiaoMi3 and other flagship\u2026|date=25 November 2013|url=https://plus.google.com/112108000562542116245/posts/e4sbTVSiPs2|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416205343/https://plus.google.com/112108000562542116245/posts/e4sbTVSiPs2|url-status=live|accessdate=15 April 2014|archivedate=16 April 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nXiaomi showcased its ceramic [[Xiaomi Mi 5|Mi 5]] on 24 February at MWC 2016. It is also equipped with [[Near-field communication|NFC]] and a mobile payment function [[Mi-Pay|Mi Pay]] launched in April 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://allchinatech.com/8652-2/|title=Xiaomi to launch Mi Pay to take on Apple Pay|date=21 April 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160424152953/http://www.allchinatech.com/8652-2/ |archivedate=24 April 2016|url-status=live|publisher=allchinatech.com|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 September 2016, Xiaomi released the Mi 5s and Mi 5s Plus.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gsmarena.com/xiaomi_launches_mi_5s_and_mi_5s_plus-news-20730.php|title=Xiaomi launches Mi 5s and Mi 5s Plus|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160928172015/http://www.gsmarena.com/xiaomi_launches_mi_5s_and_mi_5s_plus-news-20730.php|archivedate=28 September 2016|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 4 November 2016, Xiaomi released the [[Xiaomi Mi MIX|Mi MIX]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2016/10/25/13401440/xiaomi-mi-mix-concept-phone-specs-release-date-price|title=Xiaomi is selling the concept phone of your wildest dreams|website=The Verge|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171119142131/https://www.theverge.com/2016/10/25/13401440/xiaomi-mi-mix-concept-phone-specs-release-date-price|archivedate=19 November 2017|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The Mi mix is characterized by a 91.3% screen to body ratio, which was achieved by removing all the top-mounted sensors: the [[proximity sensor]] has been replaced by ultrasound, the earpiece has been replaced with a [[piezoelectric speaker]] that uses the metal frame to generate sound, and the front-facing camera is relocated to the bottom.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gsmarena.com/xiaomi_mi_mix-8400.php|title=Xiaomi Mi Mix|publisher=gsmarena.com|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170324051333/http://www.gsmarena.com/xiaomi_mi_mix-8400.php|archivedate=24 March 2017|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Xiaomi Mi 5c]] was launched on February 2017, featuring the debut of Xiaomi's in-house processor, Pinecone Surge S1.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gadgets.ndtv.com/xiaomi-mi-5c-4048|title=Xiaomi Mi 5c price, specifications, features, comparison|website=NDTV Gadgets360.com|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170328195503/http://gadgets.ndtv.com/xiaomi-mi-5c-4048|archivedate=28 March 2017|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.trustedreviews.com/news/xiaomi-mi5c-surge-s1-news-specs-release-date-price-2954175|title=Xiaomi Mi 5C: All you need to know about the Surge S1-powered phone {{!}} Trusted Reviews|date=2017-02-28|work=Trusted Reviews|access-date=2018-07-02|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n[[Xiaomi Mi 9]] was launched on 20 February 2019 in Beijing, China. This is Xiaomi's first triple camera smartphone. It is Powered By [[List of Qualcomm Snapdragon systems-on-chip|Snapdragon 855]] SoC with 8GB [[Random-access memory|RAM]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.androidleo.com/xiaomi-mi9-specs-price/|title=Xiaomi Mi 9 Full specifications, Price|date=2019-02-21|work=Androidleo.com|access-date=2019-02-21|language=en}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable mw-collapsible\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Model\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Display type\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Display size\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Resolution\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Release date\n! rowspan=\"2\" |[[Long Term Evolution|4G LTE]] support\n! rowspan=\"2\" |[[System on a chip|System on chip]]\n! rowspan=\"2\" |GPU\n! rowspan=\"2\" |[[Random-access memory|RAM]]\n! rowspan=\"2\" |User memory\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Primary camera\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Front camera\n! colspan=\"2\" |Operating system\n|-\n!When released\n!Avai