g Term Evolution|4G LTE]] support\n![[System on a chip|System on chip]]\n![[Random-access memory|RAM]]\n!Primary camera\n!Front camera\n!Operating system\n|-\n|[[Xiaomi Mi Pad|Mi Pad]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mi.com/en/mipad/#param|title=Mi Pad - Mi Global Home|publisher=mi.com|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170521211114/http://www.mi.com/en/mipad/#param|archivedate=21 May 2017|url-status=live|access-date=24 May 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|IPS\n|7.9\"\n|QXGA 2048\u00d71536\n|2014.04\n|not applicable\n|[[Tegra|Nvidia]]\n[[Tegra]] K1\n\n2x 2.2&nbsp;GHz\n|2 GB\n|8 MPx\n|5 MPx\n|MIUI v9 Android 4.4\n|-\n|Mi Pad 2<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mi.com/mipad2/specs/|title=\u5c0f\u7c73\u5e73\u677f2\u53c2\u6570 - \u5c0f\u7c73\u5546\u57ce|publisher=mi.com|language=zh-CN|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170609063719/http://www.mi.com/mipad2/specs/|archivedate=9 June 2017|url-status=live|access-date=18 June 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|IPS\n|7.9\"\n|QXGA 2048\u00d71536\n|2015.11\n|not applicable\n|[[Intel Atom|Intel]]\n[[Intel Atom|Atom]]\n\n4x 2.24&nbsp;GHz\n|2 GB\n|8 MPx\n|5 MPx\n|MIUI v9 Android 5.1\nor\n\n[[Windows 10]] Home 64bit\n|-\n|Mi Pad 3<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mi.com/mipad3/specs/|title=\u5c0f\u7c73\u5e73\u677f3\u53c2\u6570 - \u5c0f\u7c73\u5546\u57ce|publisher=mi.com|language=zh-CN|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170525095427/http://www.mi.com/mipad3/specs/|archivedate=25 May 2017|url-status=live|access-date=26 May 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|IPS\n|7.9\"\n|QXGA 2048\u00d71536\n|2017.04\n|not applicable\n|[[MediaTek|Mediatek]]\nMT8176 2x 2.1&nbsp;GHz & 4x 1.7&nbsp;GHz\n|4 GB\n|13 MPx\n|5 MPx\n|MIUI v9 Android 7.0\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | Mi Pad 4<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mi.com/mipad4/specs/|title=\u5c0f\u7c73\u5e73\u677f4\u53c2\u6570 - \u5c0f\u7c73\u5546\u57ce|website=www.mi.com|language=zh-CN|access-date=2018-06-29}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"3\" | IPS \n| rowspan=\"3\" | 8.0\"\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 1920\u00d71200\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2018.06\n| rowspan=\"2\" |not applicable\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Qualcomm Snapdragon|Qualcomm]]\n[[Snapdragon 600|Snapdragon 660]]\n\n4\u00d7 2.2&nbsp;GHz & 4\u00d7 1.84&nbsp;GHz\n|3 GB\n| rowspan=\"3\" |13 MPx\n| rowspan=\"3\" |5 MPx\n| rowspan=\"3\" |MIUI 10\nAndroid 8.1\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |4 GB\n|-\n|Yes\n|-\n| Mi Pad 4 Plus\n|IPS\n| 10.1\"\n| 1920x1200\n| 2018.08\n| Yes\n|Qualcomm\nSnapdragon 660\n\n4x 2.2 GHz & 4x 1.8 GHz\n|4GB\n|13 MPx\n|5 MPx\n|MIUI 10\nAndroid 8.1\n|}\n\n=== MiWiFi ===\nThe Xiaomi [[MiWiFi]] is a series network [[Router (computing)|routers]] initially launched on 23 April 2014. The latest in the series is a corporate-class router with built-in storage of up to 6&nbsp;TB. It is said to have a PCB dual-antenna array supporting 802.11ac Wi-Fi standard, a [[Broadcom]] 4709C dual-core 1.4&nbsp;GHz processor and 512&nbsp;MB of flash memory. The router can be used as a wireless hard drive for movies and photos, in tandem with Xiaomi's apps that feature remote downloads, automatic backups, remote access to files and other features.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gadgets.ndtv.com/internet/news/xiaomi-launches-new-mi-wi-fi-router-with-6tb-storage-and-more-702031|title=Xiaomi Launches New Mi Wi-Fi Router With 6TB Storage and More|last1=Sinha|first1=Robin|date=10 June 2015|website=NDTV Gadgets|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150610234046/http://gadgets.ndtv.com/internet/news/xiaomi-launches-new-mi-wi-fi-router-with-6tb-storage-and-more-702031|archivedate=10 June 2015|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n=== Mi TV ===\nThe MiTV is a line of [[smart TV]]s designed and marketed by Xiaomi. It runs [[Android (operating system)|Android]] and was initially announced in 2013. The latest in the series are Mi TV 3s 43 inch and the Mi TV 3s 65 inch curved. The Mi TV 3s 43 inch has a 43-inch 1920p x 1080p from either [[LG Corporation|LG]] or AUO. It has the 1.45&nbsp;GHz quad-core MStar 6A908 [[ARM Cortex-A9|Cortex-A9]] processor with [[Mali-450]] MP4 GPU, and 1&nbsp;GB DDR3 RAM and 8&nbsp;GB internal memory ([[eMMC]] 4.5).<ref name=\"fonearena.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.fonearena.com/blog/179517/xiaomi-mi-tv-3s-65-inch-curved-4k-tv-and-43-inch-full-hd-tv-announced.html|title=Xiaomi Mi TV 3S 65-inch curved 4K TV and 43-inch Full HD TV announced|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160325170246/http://www.fonearena.com/blog/179517/xiaomi-mi-tv-3s-65-inch-curved-4k-tv-and-43-inch-full-hd-tv-announced.html|archivedate=25 March 2016|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>  At 10.9&nbsp;mm, it is pretty thin for a TV.  The Mi TV 65 inch curved has a 4K Samsung display. It has a 1.4&nbsp;GHz quad-core MStar 6A928 [[Cortex-A17]] processor with Mali-760 MP4 GPU. For the memory, it has 2&nbsp;GB DDR3 RAM and 8&nbsp;GB internal memory (eMMC 50).<ref name=\"fonearena.com\" />  It is 5.9&nbsp;mm thick, but it has to have a sound bar for audio.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gsmarena.com/xiaomi_unveils_curved_65_mi_tv_3s_with_4k_samsung_screen-blog-17391.php|title=Xiaomi unveils curved 65|publisher=GSMArena.com|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160323175415/http://www.gsmarena.com/xiaomi_unveils_curved_65_mi_tv_3s_with_4k_samsung_screen-blog-17391.php|archivedate=23 March 2016|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n=== MiBox ===\n[[File:Xiaomi Mi Box S.jpg|thumb|Xiaomi Mi Box S]]\nThe Xiaomi MiBox is a [[Smart TV|smart]] [[set-top box]] for [[televisions]].<ref>{{citation|title=Mi Box|url=http://www.mi.com/en/mibox|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140530040144/http://www.mi.com/en/mibox|url-status=live|accessdate=30 May 2014|archivedate=30 May 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref> From deals struck with content providers, the set-top box offers films and TV shows with no user account nor subscription required. The box can also access content via its USB port,<ref>[https://support.kitcast.tv/support-center/how-to-connect-android-to-tv/ How to Connect Android TV Device via USB]</ref> such as through an [[external hard disk]]. Due to content licensing restrictions, it was only available in [[mainland China]] until October 2016, Xiaomi released a Mi Box running Android TV, making it accessible worldwide. In October 2018, Xiaomi released Mi Box S,<ref>[https://www.mi.com/global/mi-box-s Xiaomi Mi Box S Official Page]</ref> new version of Mi Box with [[Android TV]] Oreo.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.techradar.com/reviews/xiaomi-mi-box-s|title=Xiaomi Mi Box S review|last=accessories|first=Christian de Looper 2018-11-21T23:12:03ZAV|website=TechRadar|language=en|access-date=2019-01-28}}</ref>\n\n=== MiCloud ===\nMiCloud is a [[cloud storage]] and [[cloud computing]] service created by Xiaomi. The service allows users to store data such as contacts, messages, photos and notes on remote computer servers for download to multiple devices running MIUI operating system. The service also includes a feature that allows users to track the location of their MIUI device as well as alarm, lock or reset it.\n\n=== MiTalk ===\nMiTalk is an internet-based [[cross-platform]] [[instant messenger]] [[mobile app]] available for [[Android (operating system)|Android]] and [[iOS]] launched in 2011.<ref>{{citation|title=Welcome to Mitalk!|url=http://www.mitalk.com/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140322081456/http://www.mitalk.com/|url-status=live|accessdate=15 April 2014|archivedate=22 March 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n=== MiPower Bank ===\nMiPower Bank is a [[battery charger]] with a built-in internal battery and charges devices by USB. The chargers have an aluminium case. The [[Battery (electricity)|batteries]] rated at 5000/5200/10000/10400/16000/20000&nbsp;mAh.The 16000 & 20000&nbsp;mAh have two USB ports. [[Silicone]] sleeves are available for all, except the 20000&nbsp;mAh version.\n\n== Laptops ==\n\n=== Mi Notebook Air ===\nIn August 2016, Xiaomi launched two ultrabooks, 12.5\" and 13.3\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnet.com/products/xiaomi-mi-notebook-air/|title=Archived copy|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171215021230/https://www.cnet.com/products/xiaomi-mi-notebook-air/|archivedate=15 December 2017|url-status=live|accessdate=2018-04-06|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe 2016 12.5\" laptop had an [[Intel Core|Intel core M3]] (th generation) processor, 4&nbsp;GB DDR4 RAM and a 128&nbsp;GB [[Solid-state drive|SSD]]. The price is RMB 3,499 and officially is only sold in mainland China.\n\nThe 2016 13.3\" laptop had an Intel i5/i7 processor, 8 GB DDR4 RAM and a 256 GB [[Solid-state drive|SSD]]. It weighs 1.07&nbsp;kg and is 12.9mm thin. The price is RMB 4,999 and officially is only sold in mainland China.\n\nIn March 2017, the new 12.5\" laptop had an [[Intel Core|Intel core M3]] (7th generation) processor and a 256&nbsp;GB [[Solid-state drive|SDD]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gizmochina.com/2017/03/30/xiaomi-mi-notebook-air-12-5-processor-upgrade-256gb-storage-version/|title=Archived copy|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171220132825/https://www.gizmochina.com/2017/03/30/xiaomi-mi-notebook-air-12-5-processor-upgrade-256gb-storage-version/|archivedate=20 December 2017|url-status=live|accessdate=2018-04-06|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2018, Xiaomi released its Mi Notebook Air in Spain<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.insightportal.io/news/all-news/xiaomi-mi-notebook-air-2017-release-date-and-specifications|title=Xiaomi Mi Notebook Air 2017 Release Date and Specifications|last=Kudev|first=Stefan|date=|website=www.insightportal.io|access-date=2018-07-04}}</ref>\n\n=== Mi Notebook Air 4G ===\nXiaomi released the Mi Notebook Air 4G<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://en.miui.com/thread-448870-1-1.html|title=Xiaomi Mi Notebook Air 4G Launched: Price, Specifications, and More - Mi Notebook Air - Xiaomi MIUI Official Forum|last=Forum|first=Xiaomi MIUI Official|website=en.miui.com|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201043724/http://en.miui.com/thread-448870-1-1.html|archivedate=1 December 2017|url-status=live|access-date=24 November 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref> with built-in 4G LTE by a SIM card.\n\nThe 12.5\" laptop is powered by an Intel Core m3 processor with 4 GB of RAM and a 128 GB SSD.\n\nThe 13.3\" laptop is powered by an Intel Core i7 processor with 8 GB of RAM and a 256 GB SSD.\n\nBoth laptops support USB Type-C.\n\n=== Mi Gaming Laptop ===\nSpecifications - 15.6\" wide-color gamut ultra-thin bezels - NVIDIA Geforce GTX 1060 - 7th gen Intel Core i7 processor - 256GB SSD + 1TB HDD - Professional gaming keyboard\n\n=== Mi Notebook Pro ===\nSpecifications-15.6\" wide color gamut - NVIDIA MX150 - 8th Gen Intel Core i5/i7 processor - 256GB SSD - Long Battery Life\n\n== Mi Electric Scooter ==\nThe M365 Electric Scooter is an aluminium frame scooter (Approx. 1080mm * 430mm * 1140mm) that weighs about 12.5kg. The M365 has a maximum speed of 25km/h (max 18km/h on Cruise control) with a 250 watt rated motor (16 Nm max torque). The battery pack is made up of thirty 18650mAh lithium-ion batteries from LG, allowing for a 30 km range. (30km long-distance range on a single full charge measured under the following conditions: 75kg load, 25\u00b0C weather temperatures, flat road without strong winds, power saving mode, and 15km/h constant speeds.)<ref>{{cite web |title=Mi Electric Scooter |url=https://www.mi.com/global/mi-electric-scooter/specs |website=www.mi.com |publisher=Xiaomi |accessdate=21 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Smartwatches and Smartbands ==\n<!-- Following content have been hiddened as they are not released by Xiaomi itself\n=== AMAZFIT Smartwatches ===\nOn 30 August 2016, Xiaomi unveiled its first smartwatch the AMAZFIT Pace.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gadgetsnow.com/more-gadgets/Xiaomis-first-smartwatch-Amazfit-launched-in-China/articleshow/53931225.cms|title=Xiaomi\u2019s first smartwatch \u2018Amazfit\u2019 launched in China {{!}} Gadgets Now|website=Gadget Now|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201030633/https://www.gadgetsnow.com/more-gadgets/Xiaomis-first-smartwatch-Amazfit-launched-in-China/articleshow/53931225.cms|archivedate=1 December 2017|url-status=live|access-date=24 November 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn September 19 2018, Xiaomi released the Amazfit Verge Smartwatch.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.gizmochina.com/2018/09/17/huami-amazfit-verge-vs-amazfit-stratos-vs-amazfit-bip-specs-comparison/|title=Huami Amazfit Verge vs Amazfit Stratos vs Amazfit Bip: Specs Comparison - Gizmochina|date=2018-09-17|work=Gizmochina|access-date=2018-09-19|language=en-US}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Model\n!Display\n!Specifications\n|-\n|AmazFit\nPace<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://us.amazfit.com/shop/pace|title=Amazfit {{!}} Pace {{!}} Sports Tracking Smartwatch with GPS + Heart Rate|last=Octopus|date=21 November 2016|work=Amazfit|access-date=4 September 2017|language=en-us}}</ref>\n|Circular 1.34\" MIP, 300 x 300 pixels, touch screen\n|[[CPU]] 1.2&nbsp;GHz; [[Random-access memory|RAM]] 512MB; 4GB storage, [[Wi-Fi]], [[GPS]], Heart Rate Monitor, Pedometer, Vibration\n|-\n|AmazFit\nBip<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://cn.amazfit.com/watch-lite.html|title=AMAZFIT_\u7c73\u52a8\u624b\u8868\u9752\u6625\u7248_\u5b98\u65b9\u7f51\u7ad9|website=cn.amazfit.com|language=zh|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170904200413/http://cn.amazfit.com/watch-lite.html|archivedate=4 September 2017|url-status=live|access-date=4 September 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|1.28\" screen, 176 x 176 pixels, touch screen\n|GPS, Heart Rate Monitor, Barometer, Bluetooth, Notifications, Vibration, Pedometer\n|-\n|AmazFit\nArc<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://us.amazfit.com/shop/arc?variant=792|title=Amazfit {{!}} Arc {{!}} Heart Rate, Activity & Sleep Tracker|last=Octopus|date=26 October 2016|work=Amazfit|access-date=4 September 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170903115440/https://us.amazfit.com/shop/arc?variant=792|archivedate=3 September 2017|url-status=live|language=en-us|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|OLED, touch screen\n|Heart Rate Monitor, Pedometer, Vibration, Bluetooth\n|-\n|AmazFit\nHealth<ref>{{Cite web|