|Tunisia}}\n| subdivision_type1               = [[Governorates of Tunisia|Governorate]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Ariana Governorate]]\n| subdivision_type2               = \n| subdivision_name2               = \n| government_footnotes            = \n| name                            = Chotrana\n| nickname                        = \n| coordinates                     = {{coord|36|53|46|N|10|13|03|E|region:TN|display=inline,title}}\n}}\n\n'''Chotrana''' ({{lang-ar|\u0634\u0637\u0631\u0627\u0646\u0629}}), is a Tunisian [[village]] dependent on the municipality of [[La Soukra]], in the governorate of [[Aryanah|Arianah]].\n\n== History ==\nFrom the end of the 1970s, new inhabitants settled there from various regions of the country. Chotrana also has many emigrants who have built a second home in which they stay during the summer or after retirement.<ref>{{Citation|title=Chotrana|date=2019-12-03|url=https://fr.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Chotrana&oldid=165090096|work=Wikip\u00e9dia|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n\n* [[La Soukra]]\n* [[Ariana]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Chotrana}}\n\n[[Category:Ariana Governorate]]\n[[Category:Communes of Tunisia]]\n\n\n{{Tunisia-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n| official_name                   = Chotrana\n| other_name                      = \n| area_magnitude                  = \n| unit_pref                       = \n| area_footnotes                  = \n| area_total_km2                  = \n| area_land_km2                   = \n| population_as_of                = \n| population_footnotes            = \n| population_note                 = \n| population_total                = \n| population_density_km2          = \n| leader_name                     = \n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| utc_offset                      = +1\n| elevation_m                     = \n| elevation_ft                    = \n| postal_code_type                = \n| postal_code                     = \n| area_code                       = \n| blank_name                      = \n| blank_info                      = \n| website                         = \n| footnotes                       = \n| established_title               = \n| leader_title                    = \n| established_date                = \n| timezone                        = \n| map_caption                     = \n| pushpin_map                     = \n| settlement_type                 = Commune and town\n| motto                           = \n| image_skyline                   = VueAerienneChotrana6Aout2010.jpg\n| imagesize                       = \n| image_caption                   = aerial view Chotrana  -  August 6, 2010\n| image_flag                      = \n| flag_size                       = \n| image_seal                      = \n| seal_size                       = \n| mapsize                         = \n| government_type                 = \n| native_name                     = \n| image_map                       = \n| pushpin_label_position          = bottom\n| pushpin_mapsize                 = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = \n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = {{flag|Tunisia}}\n| subdivision_type1               = [[Governorates of Tunisia|Governorate]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Ariana Governorate]]\n| subdivision_type2               = \n| subdivision_name2               = \n| government_footnotes            = \n| name                            = Chotrana\n| nickname                        = \n| coordinates                     = {{coord|36|53|46|N|10|13|03|E|region:TN|display=inline,title}}\n}}\n\n'''Chotrana''' ({{lang-ar|\u0634\u0637\u0631\u0627\u0646\u0629}}) , is a Tunisian [[village]] dependent on the municipality of [[La Soukra]], in the governorate of [[Aryanah|Arianah]].\n\n<br />\n\n== History ==\nFrom the end of the 1970s, new inhabitants settled there from various regions of the country. Chotrana also has many emigrants who have built a second home in which they stay during the summer or after retirement.<ref>{{Citation|title=Chotrana|date=2019-12-03|url=https://fr.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Chotrana&oldid=165090096|work=Wikip\u00e9dia|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n\n* [[La Soukra]]\n* [[Ariana]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Chotrana}}\n[[Category:Ariana Governorate]]\n[[Category:Communes of Tunisia]]\n{{Tunisia-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "CAPTAIN RAJU", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up,typo(s) fixed: ,  \u2192 ,", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chotrana"}
{"title_page": "Aarogya Setu", "text_new": "{{short description|Mobile Application}}\n'''Aarogya Setu''' is a [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] tracking mobile application developed by the [[National Informatics Centre]] that comes under the [[Ministry of Electronics and Information Technology]], [[Government of India]].\n\n[[Image:Aarogya Setu.jpg|right|thumb|200px|The logo of Aarogya Setu app]]\n\n==Overview==\nThe stated purpose of this app is to spread the awareness and to connect essential health services to the people of India.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/trends/coronavirus-pandemic-govt-launches-covid-19-tracking-app-aarogya-setu-for-android-ios-users-5101621.html|title=Coronavirus pandemic {{!}} Govt launches COVID-19 tracking app 'Aarogya Setu' for Android, iOS users|website=Moneycontrol|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref><ref name=\":1\" />. This app will augment the initiatives of the Department of Health to contain the risks of COVID-19, and sharing the best practices and  advisories. This is a tracking app which uses smartphone's [[Global Positioning System|GPS]] and [[Bluetooth]] features to track the [[Coronavirus disease 2019|coronavirus]] infection. Aarogya Setu app is available for [[Android (operating system)|Android]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=nic.goi.aarogyasetu&hl=en_IN|title=Aarogya Setu \u2013 Apps on Google Play|website=play.google.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> and [[iOS]] mobile operating systems<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mygov.in/aarogya-setu-app/|title=Aarogya Setu Mobile App|website=MyGov.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>. Using bluetooth technology, the Aarogya Setu app tries to  determine the risk if one has been near a Covid-19 infected person (within six feet of distance) by scanning through a database of known cases across India, and using location information it determines the location one is in belongs to the infected areas based on the data available.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/technology/apps/govt-launches-aarogya-setu-a-coronavirus-tracker-app-all-you-need-to-know-11585821224138.html|title=Govt launches 'Aarogya Setu', a coronavirus tracker app: All you need to know|date=2020-04-02|website=Livemint|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\nThis app is an updated version of an earlier app called '''Corona Kavach''' (now discontinued) which was already released by the Government of India<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.financialexpress.com/industry/technology/govt-discontinues-corona-kavach-aarogya-setu-is-now-indias-go-to-covid-19-tracking-app/1919378/|title=Govt discontinues Corona Kavach, Aarogya Setu is now India\u2019s go-to COVID-19 tracking app|date=2020-04-05|website=The Financial Express|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> Aarogya Setu crossed five million downloads within the three days of its launch, making it one of the most popular government apps in India<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gadgets.ndtv.com/apps/news/aarogya-setu-tops-india-charts-on-app-stores-5-million-installs-in-three-days-of-launch-coronavirus-2206060|title=Aarogya Setu App Crosses 5 Million Installs in 3 Days|website=NDTV Gadgets 360|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abplive.com/news/gadgets/coronavirus-india-govts-aarogya-setu-app-crosses-5-million-downloads-in-3-days-1189576|title=Coronavirus India: Govt's 'Aarogya Setu' App Crosses 5 Million Downloads in 3 Days|last=Bureau|first=ABP News|date=2020-04-04|website=news.abplive.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\nAarogya Setu is available currently available in 11 languages<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.aarogyasetu.in/|title=Aarogya Setu App|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> (English, Hindi, Telugu, Kannada, Malayalam, Tamil, Punjabi, Bengali, Oriya, Gujarati, and Marathi) and expected to be available in more Indian languages soon. One is asked to provide health and other profiling information after signing into the app. \n\nThe app is also built on a platform that can provide Application Programming Interface<ref name=\":0\" /> ([[Application programming interface|API]]) so that other computer programs, mobile applications and web services can make use of the features and data available of Aarogya setu.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[COVID-19 apps]]\n\n== References ==\n<!-- Inline citations added to your article will automatically display here. See en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WP:REFB for instructions on how to add citations. -->\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*https://www.aartichalisa.in/aarogya-setu-app-download/\n*{{official|https://www.aarogyasetu.in}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in India}}\n\n[[Category:Mobile applications]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in India]]\n[[Category:Software associated with the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:2020 software]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Mobile Application}}\n'''Aarogya Setu''' is a [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] tracking mobile application developed by the [[National Informatics Centre]] that comes under the [[Ministry of Electronics and Information Technology]], [[Government of India]].\n\n[[Image:Aarogya Setu.jpg|right|thumb|200px|The logo of Aarogya Setu app]]\n\n==Overview==\nThe stated purpose of this app is to spread the awareness and to connect essential health services to the people of India.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/trends/coronavirus-pandemic-govt-launches-covid-19-tracking-app-aarogya-setu-for-android-ios-users-5101621.html|title=Coronavirus pandemic {{!}} Govt launches COVID-19 tracking app 'Aarogya Setu' for Android, iOS users|website=Moneycontrol|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref><ref name=\":1\" />. This app will augment the initiatives of the Department of Health to contain the risks of COVID-19, and sharing the best practices and  advisories. This is a tracking app which uses smartphone's [[Global Positioning System|GPS]] and [[Bluetooth]] features to track the [[Coronavirus disease 2019|coronavirus]] infection. Aarogya Setu app is available for [[Android (operating system)|Android]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=nic.goi.aarogyasetu&hl=en_IN|title=Aarogya Setu \u2013 Apps on Google Play|website=play.google.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> and [[iOS]] mobile operating systems<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mygov.in/aarogya-setu-app/|title=Aarogya Setu Mobile App|website=MyGov.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>. Using bluetooth technology, the Aarogya Setu app tries to  determine the risk if one has been near a Covid-19 infected person (within six feet of distance) by scanning through a database of known cases across India, and using location information it determines the location one is in belongs to the infected areas based on the data available.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/technology/apps/govt-launches-aarogya-setu-a-coronavirus-tracker-app-all-you-need-to-know-11585821224138.html|title=Govt launches 'Aarogya Setu', a coronavirus tracker app: All you need to know|date=2020-04-02|website=Livemint|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\nThis app is an updated version of an earlier app called '''Corona Kavach''' (now discontinued) which was already released by the Government of India<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.financialexpress.com/industry/technology/govt-discontinues-corona-kavach-aarogya-setu-is-now-indias-go-to-covid-19-tracking-app/1919378/|title=Govt discontinues Corona Kavach, Aarogya Setu is now India\u2019s go-to COVID-19 tracking app|date=2020-04-05|website=The Financial Express|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> Aarogya Setu crossed five million downloads within the three days of its launch, making it one of the most popular government apps in India<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gadgets.ndtv.com/apps/news/aarogya-setu-tops-india-charts-on-app-stores-5-million-installs-in-three-days-of-launch-coronavirus-2206060|title=Aarogya Setu App Crosses 5 Million Installs in 3 Days|website=NDTV Gadgets 360|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abplive.com/news/gadgets/coronavirus-india-govts-aarogya-setu-app-crosses-5-million-downloads-in-3-days-1189576|title=Coronavirus India: Govt's 'Aarogya Setu' App Crosses 5 Million Downloads in 3 Days|last=Bureau|first=ABP News|date=2020-04-04|website=news.abplive.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\nAarogya Setu is available currently available in 11 languages<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.aarogyasetu.in/|title=Aarogya Setu App|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> (English, Hindi, Telugu, Kannada, Malayalam, Tamil, Punjabi, Bengali, Oriya, Gujarati, and Marathi) and expected to be available in more Indian languages soon. One is asked to provide health and other profiling information after signing into the app. \n\nThe app is also built on a platform that can provide Application Programming Interface<ref name=\":0\" /> ([[Application programming interface|API]]) so that other computer programs, mobile applications and web services can make use of the features and data available of Aarogya setu.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[COVID-19 apps]]\n\n== References ==\n<!-- Inline citations added to your article will automatically display here. See en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WP:REFB for instructions on how to add citations. -->\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official|https://www.aarogyasetu.in}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in India}}\n\n[[Category:Mobile applications]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in India]]\n[[Category:Software associated with the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:2020 software]]\n", "name_user": "Aartichalisa", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eExternal links:Aarogya setu app download link)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedi